---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Refactored QStash docs"
  description="Documentation work for QStash messaging, scheduling, SDKs, and API examples."
>
  <article class="p-6 lg:p-12 max-w-3xl mx-auto">
    <a href="/shipped" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 text-sm text-charcoal-muted dark:text-sand-muted hover:text-accent dark:hover:text-accent-light transition-colors mb-8">
      <svg class="w-4 h-4" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
        <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M7 16l-4-4m0 0l4-4m-4 4h18" />
      </svg>
      Back to shipped work
    </a>

    <header class="mb-10">
      <div class="case-cover mb-8"><span>Cover image</span></div>
      <p class="text-sm text-accent dark:text-accent-light font-medium mb-4 tracking-wide uppercase">Upstash · QStash</p>
      <h1 class="font-serif text-4xl md:text-5xl font-semibold text-balance leading-tight">Refactored QStash docs</h1>
      <p class="mt-5 text-lg leading-relaxed text-charcoal-muted dark:text-sand-muted">
        I refactored QStash documentation to make messaging, scheduling, SDK usage, and API examples easier for developers to find and apply.
      </p>
      <div class="mt-6 flex flex-wrap gap-3">
        <a href="https://upstash.com/docs/qstash/overall/getstarted" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="btn btn-ghost border border-cream-300 dark:border-ink-lighter">QStash docs</a>
        <a href="https://upstash.com/docs/qstash/overall/apiexamples" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="btn btn-ghost border border-cream-300 dark:border-ink-lighter">API examples</a>
        <a href="https://upstash.com/docs/qstash/sdks/ts/overview" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="btn btn-ghost border border-cream-300 dark:border-ink-lighter">TypeScript SDK docs</a>
      </div>
    </header>

    <div class="prose prose-lg dark:prose-invert max-w-none">
      <h2>Problem</h2>
      <p>
        QStash spans publishing, scheduling, retries, SDKs, URL groups, DLQs, and API references. As the
        product grew, the docs needed clearer paths for developers trying to move from a first publish to
        more advanced production workflows.
      </p>

      <h2>What I Worked On</h2>
      <p>
        I reorganized and refined QStash documentation around the way developers actually use the product:
        getting started, choosing an SDK, publishing messages, using API examples, and understanding more
        advanced features like batching and scheduling.
      </p>

      <h2>Outcome</h2>
      <p>
        The refactor made the documentation easier to scan and reduced friction for developers integrating
        QStash into serverless messaging and scheduling workflows.
      </p>
    </div>
  </article>
</Layout>

<style>
  .case-cover { display: grid; min-height: 18rem; place-items: center; border: 1px solid rgb(232 224 208); border-radius: 0.5rem; background: linear-gradient(135deg, rgba(47, 111, 159, 0.2) 25%, transparent 25%) 0 0 / 24px 24px, linear-gradient(135deg, transparent 75%, rgba(47, 111, 159, 0.16) 75%) 0 0 / 24px 24px, rgb(245 240 232); }
  :global(.dark) .case-cover { border-color: rgb(37 36 34); background: linear-gradient(135deg, rgba(59, 126, 161, 0.24) 25%, transparent 25%) 0 0 / 24px 24px, linear-gradient(135deg, transparent 75%, rgba(59, 126, 161, 0.18) 75%) 0 0 / 24px 24px, rgb(37 36 34); }
  .case-cover span { font-family: "JetBrains Mono", monospace; color: rgb(74 74 74); font-size: 0.75rem; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.08em; }
  :global(.dark) .case-cover span { color: rgb(184 180 172); }
</style>
